OL,3,CPaul Pogba hit with four-year ban for
OL,4,Cdoping offence
OL,6,FPaul Pogba has been banned from
OL,7,Ffootball for four years for a doping
OL,8,Foffence, it has been reported.
OL,10,FThe former midfielder was suspended
OL,11,Ffrom his current club, Juventus, in
OL,12,FSeptember 2023 when he tested positive
OL,13,Ffor DHEA, a substance that promotes
OL,14,Fthe production of testosterone.
OL,16,FThe ruling means Pogba will be unable
OL,17,Fto play until 2027, when he will be
OL,18,F33, with the ban backdated to the date
OL,19,Fof the failed test.
